Another CTF question done, quite an easy one, needed basic terminal knowledge to solve it.
A total of 5 basic commands were used to solve it.
The question was : https://learn.cylabacademy.org/library/766?page=1&category=5
It took a total of five basic terminal commands to get the flag:
1. command to decode the base64 encoded flag.
2. command to reverse the string.
3. command to replace '-' to '_'
4. command to replace '()' to '{}'
5. command to convert the expression recovered from step 4 into the final flag, i.e, ROT13 to letters.
Sneak peek of the flag :  picoCTF{Revers1ng_...
